.el .ds Aq '
.TH wafrift 1  "wafrift 0.2.13" 
.SH NAME
wafrift \- WAF evasion toolkit — run without arguments for interactive mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBwafrift\fR [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
WAF evasion toolkit — run without arguments for interactive mode.
.PP
Exit codes (CI\-friendly):
0  success
1  generic error (bad input, IO, etc.)
2  bench\-waf: zero bypasses on any case in \-\-evade mode
2  replay:    saved bypass got blocked (regression signal)
3  bench\-diff: regression vs baseline (see \-\-bypass\-drop\-pp)
4  bench\-waf \-\-validate\-only: corpus integrity errors
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress human\-readable output — emit only machine\-parseable results (JSON)
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fI<CONFIG>\fR
Path to a TOML config file. Default: `.wafrift.toml` in CWD or `~/.config/wafrift/config.toml`
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
wafrift\-evade(1)
Transform a payload with evasion techniques
.TP
wafrift\-detect(1)
Identify a WAF from response metadata
.TP
wafrift\-probe(1)
Generate differential analysis probes
.TP
wafrift\-scan(1)
Fire evasion variants against a live target and report bypass results
.TP
wafrift\-bench\-waf(1)
Reproducible WAF benchmark: measure raw block rate AND wafrift bypass rate. Pass `\-\-evade` to actually run the evasion engine (off by default — without it, only the WAF\*(Aqs raw rejection rate is measured, no bypass claim is made)
.TP
wafrift\-bench\-diff(1)
Compare two `bench\-waf \-\-output` JSON blobs and gate on regression
.TP
wafrift\-origin\-hints(1)
DNS hints for `origin_bypass` (authorized targets only)
.TP
wafrift\-egress\-example(1)
Print JSON snippets for egress presets (e.g. Tor SOCKS)
.TP
wafrift\-techniques(1)
List or explain available technique selectors for `\-\-only`/`\-\-exclude`
.TP
wafrift\-completion(1)
Generate shell completions for bash, zsh, fish, or PowerShell
.TP
wafrift\-recon(1)
Origin discovery via crt.sh + DNS (authorized targets only)
.TP
wafrift\-discover(1)
Endpoint discovery: parse OpenAPI/Swagger, run GraphQL introspection, or fire differential parameter mining. Emits `DiscoveredEndpoint` JSON suitable for piping into `wafrift scan \-\-from\-discovery`
.TP
wafrift\-replay(1)
Replay a saved bypass against a target — proves reproducibility
.TP
wafrift\-report(1)
Generate a markdown findings report from the proxy gene bank
.TP
wafrift\-init(1)
Scaffold a `.wafrift.toml` config in the current directory
.TP
wafrift\-seed(1)
Pre\-load a gene\-bank with known\-working techniques (per\-WAF or per\-host)
.TP
wafrift\-import\-curl(1)
Take a curl invocation (e.g. from Burp\*(Aqs "Copy as cURL"), run scan against the parsed target
.TP
wafrift\-bank(1)
Manage gene\-banks: list / export / import
.TP
wafrift\-bypass\-probe(1)
Differential bypass scanner against a single protected URL. Fires 136 auth\-bypass header probes + path\-routing\-disagreement variants + HTTP method overrides; reports any probe that diverges from the baseline response. The Tsai\-class vuln finder
.TP
wafrift\-man(1)
Generate a troff man page for `wafrift` (and optionally subcommands)
.TP
wafrift\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.2.13
